          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Currents ranging from 70 to 200 n-A were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma rays were detected with a 23 cm",
                "diameter by 23 cm long NaI(Tl) crystal surrounded",
                "by a plastic scintillator operated in anticoincidence.",
                "A cylindrical lead collimator, 7.6 cm in diameter, with",
                "its end face 60.8 cm from the target, was placed in",
                "front of the NaI crystal subtending an angle of +-3.6",
                "degr. at the 13C target. The spectrometer was enclosed",
                "in a 10 cm thick lead shield and surrounded by a 55 cm",
                "thick boron loaded paraffin layer to minimize",
                "background radiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "13C self-supporting foils was used. The 13C foils were",
                "obtained by mixing 97.6% isotopically enriched 13C with",
                "alcodag (a colloidal suspension of graphite in",
                "alcohol). Below 5.74 MeV a target with a 1.032 mg/cm2",
                "thick was used. For the measurement of the angular",
                "distributions and the yield curve at higher energies, a",
                "1.35 mg/cm2 thick target was employed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "An absolute determination of the differential cross",
                "section at 90 degr. was obtained with a gas target",
                "filled with methane enriched in 13C to 90%. Both the",
                "13C foils and the gas target were mounted in a glass",
                "chamber with a wall thickness of approximately 0.28 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
